%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221492%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EVolunteers%20and%20staff%20serve%20food%20to%20people%20in%20New%20York%20on%20May%206%2C%202023.%3Cp%3ESelcuk%20Acar%2FAnadolu%20Agency%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%20%3Cli%3E3.5%20million%20more%20US%20households%20were%20food%20insecure%20in%202022%2C%20a%20recent%20report%20showed.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EElevated%20food%20prices%20could%20be%20one%20reason%2C%20said%20Chloe%20East%2C%20a%20visiting%20fellow%20at%20the%20Hamilton%20Project%20at%20Brookings.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EThere%20was%20also%20an%20increase%20in%20food%20insecurity%20for%20households%20with%20children%20from%202021%20to%202022.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAbout%203.5%20million%20more%20US%20households%20were%20food%20insecure%20for%20at%20least%20part%20of%202022%20than%20in%202021.%20The%20increase%20is%20the%20biggest%20uptick%20since%20the%202008%20financial%20crisis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20according%20to%20a%20new%20US%20Department%20of%20Agriculture%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ers.usda.gov%2Fpublications%2Fpub-details%2F%3Fpubid%3D107702%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Food%20insecurity%20is%20when%20the%20%26quot%3Bability%20to%20acquire%20adequate%20food%20is%20limited%20by%20a%20lack%20of%20money%20and%20other%20resources%2C%26quot%3B%20per%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAround%2017%20million%20households%2C%20or%2012.8%25%20of%20US%20households%2C%20were%20food%20insecure%20in%202022.%20Additionally%2C%2044.2%20million%20people%20were%20in%20food-insecure%20households%20in%202022%2C%20soaring%20from%2033.8%20million%20in%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22raw%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FRFrKo%2F2%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Number%20of%20food%20insecure%20households%20in%20the%20US%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22450%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EAlmost%207%20million%20households%20were%20considered%20%26quot%3Bvery%20low%20food%20security%26quot%3B%20households%2C%20which%20the%20report%20defined%20as%20meaning%20%26quot%3Bone%20or%20more%20household%20members%20experience%20reduced%20food%20intake%20and%20disrupted%20eating%20patterns%20at%20times%20during%20the%20year%20because%20of%20limited%20money%20and%20other%20resources%20for%20obtaining%20food.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChloe%20East%2C%20a%20visiting%20fellow%20at%20the%20Hamilton%20Project%20at%20Brookings%20and%20an%20associate%20professor%20of%20economics%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Colorado%20Denver%2C%20talked%20to%20Insider%20about%20why%20food%20insecurity%20in%20America%20may%20have%20soared.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20that%20the%20increase%20that%20we%20saw%20between%202021%20and%202022%20is%20striking%20and%20worrisome%2C%20but%20probably%20not%20surprising%20given%20changes%20in%20government-transfer%20policy%20and%20inflation%20that%20we've%20seen%20in%20the%20last%20couple%20of%20years%20in%20the%20US%2C%26quot%3B%20East%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEast%20said%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bls.gov%2Fcpi%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efood%20inflation%3C%2Fa%3E%20%26quot%3Bcertainly%20had%20an%20impact%20on%20households'%20budgets%20and%20households'%20ability%20to%20maintain%20an%20adequate%20and%20nutritious%20diet%20as%20well.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22raw%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2F8Kg9T%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Food%20inflation%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22450%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20mitigating%20factor%20East%20highlighted%20%26quot%3Bwas%20a%20big%20reevaluation%20of%20the%20SNAP%20program%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20translated%20to%20a%20rise%20in%20the%20benefit%20amounts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20it's%20clear%20that%20we%20would've%20seen%20an%20even%20larger%20increase%20in%20food%20insecurity%20in%202022%20if%20we%20hadn't%20seen%20that%20meaningful%20jump%20up%20in%20SNAP%20benefits%2C%26quot%3B%20East%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELauren%20Hall%2C%20research%20analyst%20with%20the%20food%20assistance%20division%20at%20the%20Center%20on%20Budget%20and%20Policy%20Priorities%2C%20told%20Insider%20food%20insecurity%20was%20pretty%20stable%20during%202019%20to%202021%2C%20%26quot%3Bwhich%20is%20surprising%20in%20some%20ways%20because%20we%20would've%20expected%20maybe%20a%20larger%20increase%20because%20of%20how%20difficult%20we%20knew%20food%20hardship%20was%20during%20the%20pandemic.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20could%20have%20been%20due%20to%20pandemic-relief%20programs%2C%20Hall%20said%2C%20like%20the%20expanded%20child%20tax%20credit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20uptick%20in%20food%20insecurity%20also%20occurred%20at%20a%20time%20when%20significant%20safety%20net%20enhancements%20that%20helped%20people%20through%20the%20worst%20of%20the%20pandemic%20began%20to%20end%2C%20including%20the%20expanded%20Child%20Tax%20Credit%2C%20universally%20free%20school%20meals%2C%20and%2C%20in%20a%20number%20of%20states%2C%20higher%20SNAP%20benefits%2C%26quot%3B%20Tom%20Vilsack%2C%20US%20secretary%20of%20agriculture%2C%20said%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.usda.gov%2Fmedia%2Fpress-releases%2F2023%2F10%2F25%2Fstatement-agriculture-secretary-tom-vilsack-economic-research%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estatement%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EFood%20insecurity%20soared%20in%20households%20with%20children%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20USDA%20report%20noted%20that%20kids%20%26quot%3Bare%20usually%20shielded%20from%20the%20disrupted%20eating%20patterns%20and%20reduced%20food%20intake%20that%20characterize%20very%20low%20food%20security%2C%26quot%3B%20many%20children%20saw%20food%20insecurity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20found%20381%2C000%20households%20had%20children%20facing%20very%20low%20food%20security%20in%202022%2C%20up%20from%20274%2C000%20households.%20That%20means%20%26quot%3Bchildren%20were%20hungry%2C%20skipped%20a%20meal%2C%20or%20did%20not%20eat%20for%20a%20whole%20day%20because%20there%20was%20not%20enough%20money%20for%20food%26quot%3B%20in%20these%20households%20per%20the%20report.%20The%20report%20also%20noted%20783%2C000%20kids%20%26quot%3Blived%20in%20households%20with%20very%20low%20food%20security%20among%20children%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20is%20more%20than%20the%202021%20figure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHall%20said%20the%2040%25%20increase%20in%20food%20insecurity%20for%20households%20with%20children%2C%20from%204.6%20million%20households%20to%206.4%20million%20households%2C%20was%20also%20discouraging%20given%20the%20large%20fall%20in%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAll%20of%20a%20sudden%20we%20see%20an%20increase%20quite%20high%2C%20largely%20related%20to%20food%20prices%20and%20the%20end%20of%20the%20pandemic%20programs%2C%26quot%3B%20Hall%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20shows%20us%20that%20hardship%2C%20whether%20that's%20poverty%2C%20whether%20that's%20food%20insecurity%2C%20is%20a%20policy%20choice%20and%20we%20as%20a%20country%20can%20decide%20whether%20or%20not%20we%20want%20to%20address%20these%20issues%20or%20not%2C%20whether%20we%20want%20to%20provide%20support%20for%20people%20or%20not%2C%20and%20we%20have%20a%20responsibility%20to%20do%20so%2C%26quot%3B%20Hall%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EMaking%20sure%20SNAP%20benefits%20and%20programs%20are%20accessible%20could%20help%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20measure%20Hall%20pointed%20to%20help%20bring%20food%20insecurity%20down%20in%20the%20US%20is%20focusing%20on%20the%20Special%20Supplemental%20Nutrition%20Program%20for%20Women%2C%20Infants%2C%20and%20Children%20or%20WIC%2C%20which%20is%20in%20%26quot%3Bdanger%20of%20not%20being%20fully%20funded%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%2025%20years.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20is%20making%20sure%20people%20who%20need%20SNAP%20can%20get%20assistance%2C%20per%20Hall.%20That%20includes%20loosening%20the%20work%20requirement%20needed%20for%20SNAP%20benefits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20some%20provisions%20that%20are%20being%20proposed%20that%20would%20make%20that%20work%20requirement%20even%20more%20difficult%20for%20people%20to%20meet%20or%20it%20would%20make%20it%20so%20that%20the%20work%20reporting%20requirement%20applies%20to%20more%20people%20and%20would%20basically%20reduce%20access%20to%20the%20program%2C%26quot%3B%20Hall%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHall%20also%20noted%20there%20was%20a%20revision%20a%20few%20years%20ago%20made%20to%20the%20Thrifty%20Food%20Plan%2C%20which%20is%20%26quot%3Bused%20to%20determine%20SNAP%20benefit%20amounts%26quot%3B%20per%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fns.usda.gov%2Fsnap%2Fthriftyfoodplan%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUSDA%20website%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Hall%20said%20without%20further%20updates%2C%20the%20benefits%20wouldn't%20%26quot%3Bhave%20as%20much%20purchasing%20power%20for%20families%20as%20they%20currently%20do.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20experience%20of%20the%20pandemic%20showed%20us%20that%20when%20government%20invests%20in%20meaningful%20support%20for%20families%2C%20we%20can%20make%20a%20positive%20impact%20on%20food%20security%2C%20even%20during%20challenging%20economic%20times%2C%26quot%3B%20Vilsack%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhunger-food-insecurity-child-tax-credit-inflation-rate-prices-snap-2023-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698832861000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6541043e96f7540cd06a1959%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhunger-food-insecurity-child-tax-credit-inflation-rate-prices-snap-2023-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Food%20insecurity%20in%20America%20increased%20by%20around%203.5%20million%20to%2017%20million%20food-insecure%20households%20in%202022%2C%20or%2012.8%25%20of%20households.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Madison%20Hoff)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhunger-food-insecurity-child-tax-credit-inflation-rate-prices-snap-2023-11%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20Biden%20Administration%20wants%20to%20close%20a%20retirement%20savings%20'loophole'%20that%20could%20be%20costing%20you%2020%25%20on%20your%20investments%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Biden%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6510872ce4e6ee001901c04c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPresident%20Joe%20Biden.%3Cp%3EAP%20Photo%2FAlex%20Brandon%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20Biden%20administration%20is%20proposing%20a%20new%20rule%20to%20ensure%20people%20saving%20for%20retirement%20get%20the%20best%20advice%20possible.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ECurrently%2C%20investors%20might%20be%20losing%20up%20to%20%245%20billion%20a%20year%20on%20investments%2C%20the%20administration%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20new%20rule%20is%20already%20running%20into%20pushback%2C%20and%20follows%20a%20failed%20Obama%20effort.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Biden%20administration%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbiden-new-plan-to-save-renters-from-bogus-apartment-fees-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econtinuing%3C%2Fa%3E%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fis-biden-banning-junk-fees-hidden-costs-plane-concert-tickets-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecrackdown%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fonline-shopping-hidden-junk-fees-getting-worse-sneakier-prices-tickets-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejunk%20fees%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20and%20this%20time%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbidens-big-stimulus-bill-helps-pay-pensions-2-years-later-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eretirement%20savings%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20in%20the%20limelight.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dol.gov%2Fagencies%2Febsa%2Fabout-ebsa%2Four-activities%2Fresource-center%2Ffact-sheets%2Fretirement-security-proposed-rule-and-proposed-amendments-to-class-pte-for-investment-advice-fiduciaries%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enew%20proposed%20rule%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fyou-might-be-eligible-for-overtime-pay-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDepartment%20of%20Labor%3C%2Fa%3E%20would%20close%20what%20the%20administration%20calls%20%26quot%3Bloopholes%26quot%3B%20in%20retirement%20advice%2C%20potentially%20saving%20retirees%20billions.%20DOL%20is%20proposing%20requirements%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethat%20retirement%20advisers%20give%20advice%20that's%20in%20the%20best%20interest%20of%20retirees%2C%20rather%20than%20pushing%20products%20that%20they%20might%20profit%20from.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMost%20financial%20advisors%20give%20their%20clients%20good%20advice%20at%20a%20fair%20price%20and%20are%20honest%20with%20'em%2C%20but%20that's%20not%20always%20the%20case%2C%26quot%3B%20Biden%20said%20in%20Tuesday%20remarks.%20However%2C%20some%20advisers%20steer%20their%20clients%20towards%20what's%20best%20for%20them%2C%20not%20the%20retirement%20savers%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey're%20putting%20their%20self-interest%20ahead%20of%20their%20clients'%20best%20interest%2C%20and%20they're%20scamming%20Americans%20out%20of%20hard%20earned%20money%2C%26quot%3B%20Biden%20said.%20%26quot%3BPeople%20should%20be%20able%20to%20trust%20that%20when%20they%20get%20advice%20from%20a%20so-called%20expert%2C%20they're%20getting%20real%20help%2C%20not%20getting%20ripped%20off.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBiden%20said%20that%20the%20new%20rule%20would%20mean%20that%2C%20should%20advisers%20breach%20their%20fiduciary%20duty%2C%20they%20could%20face%20%26quot%3Bserious%20penalties%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20including%20restitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECurrently%2C%20the%20Securities%20and%20Exchange%20Commission%20has%20regulations%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Ffiduciary-duty%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Emandating%20that%20investment%20advice%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20needs%20to%20be%20in%20a%20saver's%20best%20interest.%20The%20Department%20of%20Labor%20similarly%20regulated%20who%20can%20give%20retirement%20advice%20in%201975%2C%20but%20the%20ways%20that%20Americans%20save%20for%20retirement%20has%20changed%2C%20and%2C%20as%20the%20Biden%20administration%20notes%2C%20that%20means%20that%20some%20practices%20%E2%80%94%20like%20one-time%20advice%20for%20rolling%20over%20a%20401k%20%E2%80%94%20aren't%20covered.%20For%20instance%2C%20an%20adviser%20might%20give%20the%20advice%20to%20buy%20a%20fixed%20annuity%2C%20a%20popular%20retirement%20option%2C%20and%20would%20likely%20not%20be%20subject%20to%20SEC%20regulations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20where%20the%20new%20rule%20is%20meant%20to%20come%20into%20play%3A%20It'll%20expand%20the%20definition%20of%20who%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eis%20subject%20to%20the%20best%20advice%20standard.%20The%20White%20House%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.whitehouse.gov%2Fbriefing-room%2Fstatements-releases%2F2023%2F10%2F31%2Ffact-sheet-president-biden-to-announce-new-actions-to-protect-retirement-security-by-cracking-down-on-junk-fees-in-retirement-investment-advice%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eestimates%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20new%20rule%20could%20mean%20savers%20