%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E9.6%20million%20job%20openings%3C%2Fa%3E%20nationwide%20and%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Farindube%2Fstatus%2F1715101591995371585%3Fs%3D46%26t%3D2AJsaTiROqndjHD0Z5WOlw%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewhat%20economists%20are%20calling%20%26quot%3Bfull%20employment.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20Over%20the%20next%20decade%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bls.gov%2Fnews.release%2Fpdf%2Fecopro.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20US%20Bureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics%3C%2Fa%3E%20forecasts%20that%20the%20fastest-growing%20occupations%20will%20be%20in%20healthcare%2C%20transportation%2C%20renewable%20energy%2C%20and%20high-tech%20manufacturing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22raw%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FFoIpD%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Blue-collar%20jobs%20are%20seeing%20a%20boom%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22990%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3ENearly%20half%20of%20all%20job%20gains%20will%20come%20from%20the%20healthcare%20and%20social-support%20sectors.%20By%202032%2C%20one%20out%20of%20six%20new%20workers%20will%20be%20a%20home-health%20or%20personal-care%20aide.%20Construction%2C%20which%20has%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffinance.yahoo.com%2Fnews%2Fconstruction-job-market-is-red-hot-amid-persistent-inventory-shortages-184303806.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eadded%2015%2C000%20jobs%20a%20month%20over%20the%20past%20year%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20also%20has%20room%20to%20keep%20expanding.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20manufacturing%20jobs%20as%20a%20whole%20are%20expected%20to%20stay%20flat%2C%20spending%20in%20this%20industry%20has%20boomed%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffred.stlouisfed.org%2Fseries%2FTLMFGCONS%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%24200%20billion%3C%2Fa%3E%20each%20year%2C%20tripling%20in%20the%20past%20five%20years.%20And%20certain%20sectors%20are%20expected%20to%20grow%3A%20The%20electrical-equipment%20and%20semiconductor%20industry%20is%20projected%20to%20reach%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bls.gov%2Fnews.release%2Fpdf%2Fecopro.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E3%25%20annual%20growth%20over%20the%20next%20decade%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Chip%20manufacturing%20will%20continue%20to%20be%20a%20national%20priority%2C%20and%20that%20means%20a%20lot%20of%20well-paid%20jobs%20that%20require%20only%20a%20high-school%20education.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20going%20to%20be%20significant%20demand%20in%20manufacturing%20for%20the%20sorts%20of%20non-BA%20technician%20jobs%2C%26quot%3B%20Mark%20Muro%2C%20an%20expert%20on%20technology%20and%20workforce%20development%20and%20a%20policy%20director%20at%20the%20Brookings%20Institution%2C%20told%20me.%20Within%20chip%20manufacturing%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.brookings.edu%2Farticles%2Fwith-high-tech-manufacturing-plants-promising-good-jobs-in-ohio-workforce-developers-race-to-get-ready%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eroughly%2050%25%20of%20entry-level%20workers%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20only%20a%20high-school%20or%20equivalent%20education%20level%2C%20compared%20with%2038%25%20for%20all%20other%20industries.%20Over%20the%20next%2010%20years%2C%20as%20the%20global%20semiconductor%20industry%20is%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mckinsey.com%2Findustries%2Fsemiconductors%2Four-insights%2Fthe-semiconductor-decade-a-trillion-dollar-industry%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprimed%20to%20reach%20%241%20trillion%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20another%2050%2C000%20American%20jobs%20will%20be%20added%20for%20roles%20such%20as%20electrical%20assemblers%20and%20industrial%20technicians.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cq%3EDespite%20inflation%2C%20real%20wages%20are%20higher%20for%20blue-collar%2C%20nonmanagerial%2C%20and%20lower-%20and%20middle-wage%20workers%20than%20they%20were%20before%20the%20pandemic.%3C%2Fq%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20not%20all%20working-class%20jobs%20will%20be%20safe%20from%20automation%20%E2%80%94%20retail%20workers%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20do%20not%20have%20a%20rosy%20outlook%20%E2%80%94%20there%20has%20been%20improvement%20across%20the%20board%20for%20lower-income%20workers.%20The%20initial%20shock%20of%20the%20pandemic%20hit%20low-wage%20workers%20the%20hardest%2C%20but%20the%20recovery%20since%20has%20been%20more%20auspicious.%20Wages%20have%20grown%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.epi.org%2Fpublication%2Fswa-wages-2022%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enearly%20three%20times%20as%20fast%20as%20in%20any%20other%20%3C%2Fa%3Erecovery%20period.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.politico.com%2Fnews%2F2023%2F05%2F29%2Flow-income-wages-employment-00097135%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20wages%20of%20the%20lowest%2010th%20percentile%20of%20the%20workforce%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20earning%20an%20average%20of%20%2412.50%20an%20hour%20%E2%80%94%20grew%20only%203.9%25%20from%202009%20to%202017.%20But%20from%20March%202020%20to%20March%202022%2C%20wages%20grew%20by%205.7%25.%20Despite%20inflation%2C%20real%20wages%20are%20higher%20for%20blue-collar%2C%20nonmanagerial%2C%20and%20lower-%20and%20middle-wage%20workers%20than%20they%20were%20before%20the%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20economic%20barometers%20also%20show%20steady%20improvements%20that%20are%20likely%20to%20continue.%20Over%20the%20past%20decade%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.census.gov%2Flibrary%2Fpublications%2F2023%2Fdemo%2Fp60-280.html%23%3A~%3Atext%3DHighlights-%2COfficial%2520Poverty%2520Measure%2Cand%2520Table%2520A%252D1).%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epoverty%20rate%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20America%20has%20fallen%20from%2014.8%25%20to%2011.5%25.%20The%20net%20worth%20of%20the%20average%20household%20in%20the%20bottom%2050%25%20of%20Americans%20is%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffred.stlouisfed.org%2Fgraph%2F%3Fgraph_id%3D1101676%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eup%20more%20than%2045%25%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20before%20the%20pandemic.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20a%20recession%20is%20averted%2C%20the%20continuation%20of%20a%20tight%20labor%20market%20will%20continue%20to%20drive%20wages%20up%2C%20further%20reduce%20the%20poverty%20rate%2C%20and%20boost%20household%20income%20and%20net%20worth.%20Adding%20to%20the%20tailwinds%20is%20AI's%20adoption%2C%20which%20is%20likely%20to%20augment%20these%20jobs%2C%20leading%20to%20higher%20productivity%20growth%20over%20the%20coming%20decade.%20Increased%20labor%20productivity%20in%20the%20construction%20industry%20would%20be%20a%20boon%20for%20economic%20growth%20since%20housing%20scarcity%20remains%20one%20of%20the%20most%20pressing%20issues%20for%20Americans.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWho's%20safe%20from%20AI%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww3.weforum.org%2Fdocs%2FWEF_Jobs_of_Tomorrow_Generative_AI_2023.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWorld%20Economic%20Forum's%20recent%20joint%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20Accenture%2C%2019%2C000%20individual%20tasks%20across%20nearly%20900%20occupations%20were%20analyzed%20for%20how%20much%20they%20could%20be%20affected%20by%20AI.%20The%20findings%20were%20pretty%20straightforward%3A%20Jobs%20with%20a%20high%20degree%20of%20personal%20interaction%20and%20nonroutine%20physical%20tasks%20faced%20the%20least%20amount%20of%20disruption%20from%20AI.%20Other%20recent%20projections%20by%20the%20Bureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics%20and%20McKinsey%20have%20come%20to%20similar%20conclusions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22raw%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FYxf48%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22How%20different%20sectors%20will%20be%20impacted%20by%20AI%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22866%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20characterizes%20the%20physical%20labor%20jobs%20that%20are%20safe%20for%20the%20next%20five%20or%2010%20years%20are%20things%20that%20are%20in%20an%20unpredictable%20physical%20environment%2C%26quot%3B%20Kweilin%20Ellingrud%2C%20a%20McKinsey%20Global%20Institute%20director%2C%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BIf%20it's%20in%20a%20predictable%20physical%20environment%2C%20and%20it's%20repetitive%2C%20then%20either%20a%20robot%20%E2%80%94%20likely%20even%20before%20generative%20AI%20%E2%80%94%20or%20some%20sort%20of%20generative%20AI%20can%20create%20the%20automation%20to%20do%20that%20well.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20influential%20explanation%20for%20this%20is%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fide.mit.edu%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F08%2FIdentifying-the-Multiple-Skills-in-SBTC-8-2-19.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eknown%20as%20skill-biased%20technological%20change%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20theory%20that%20says%20routine%20roles%20that%20are%20susceptible%20to%20automation%20and%20computerization%20will%20see%20declining%20wages%2C%20while%20nonroutine%20roles%20that%20require%20dexterity%20or%20human%20interaction%20will%20see%20increased%20demand%20and%20wages.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22raw%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2Fax8Ma%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Winners%20and%20losers%20of%20AI%20%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22530%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20what%20recent%20research%20has%20found%3A%20Jobs%20such%20as%20air-conditioning%20installer%2C%20teacher%2C%20and%20hairdresser%20%E2%80%94%20jobs%20that%20are%20not%20routine%20%E2%80%94%20will%20be%20relatively%20unscathed%20over%20the%20next%20five%20to%2010%20years.%20Research%20led%20by%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F08%2F24%2Fupshot%2Fartificial-intelligence-jobs.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOpenAI%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%204%25%20of%20workers%2C%20including%20painters%2C%20carpenters%2C%20and%20roofers%2C%20had%20zero%20tasks%20that%20could%20be%20influenced%20by%20AI.%20And%20even%20though%20technology%20could%20infiltrate%20more%20of%20these%20roles%2C%20they%20fundamentally%20cannot%20be%20replaced%20by%20machines.%20Ellingrud%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BEven%20though%20we%20have%20Roombas%2C%20we%20still%20have%20house%20cleaners%20because%20the%20Roomba%20can%20only%20do%20so%20much%20and%20isn't%20all%20that%20effective.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%20of%20replacing%20these%20jobs%2C%20AI%20will%20likely%20benefit%20specific%20roles%20by%20making%20it%20easier%20to%20do%20the%20most%20routine%20parts%20of%20the%20job.%20Nurses%2C%20for%20example%2C%20could%20spend%20less%20time%20collecting%20and%20entering%20information%20into%20a%20medical-record%20system.%20For%20an%20industry%20notorious%20for%20high%20hourly%20billing%20rates%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mckinsey.com%2Ffeatured-insights%2Fmckinsey-explainers%2Fwhats-the-future-of-generative-ai-an-early-view-in-15-charts%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eallowing%20nurses%20to%20redeploy%20their%20time%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20more%20critical%20tasks%20%E2%80%94%20such%20as%20taking%20care%20of%20patients%20%E2%80%94%20would%20save%20Americans%20billions%20in%20annual%20healthcare%20costs.%20Similarly%2C%20the%20construction%20industry%20could%20benefit%20from%20new%20technology%20such%20as%20AI%20drones%20to%20do%20inspections%20or%20AI%20sensors%20that%20measure%20things%2C%20freeing%20up%20workers%20to%20do%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20may%20get%20a%20bifurcation%20within%20these%20groups%20where%20the%20hands-on%20physical%20work%20remains%2C%20but%20generative%20AI%20picks%20up%20and%20substitutes%20for%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20management%20supervising%2C%26quot%3B%20Muro%20told%20me.%20He%20added%3A%20%26quot%3BThere%20are%20these%20jobs%20that%20are%20in%20a%20middle%20ground%20where%20the%20physical%20work%20may%20remain%20but%20the%20supervision%20might%20be%20more%20exposed.%26quot%3B%20But%20instead%20of%20replacing%20workers%2C%20this%20kind%20of%20integration%20could%20help%20these%20types%20of%20roles%20be%20more%20productive%2C%20have%20more%20demand%2C%20and%20earn%20more%20money.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ESafe%20ground%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBlue-collar%20jobs%20are%20not%20only%20safe%20from%20AI's%20impact%20but%20also%20physically%20safer%20with%20the%20tech.%20AI's%20adoption%20in%20the%20workplace%20can%20help%20improve%20safety%20via%20real-time%20monitoring%20of%20risks%20and%20alerts%20for%20equipment%20issues%20or%20injuries.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bls.gov%2Fopub%2Fted%2F2023%2Fa-look-at-workplace-deaths-and-nonfatal-injuries-and-illnesses-for-workers-memorial-day.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEach%20year%20in%20the%20US%2C%20there%20are%202.7%20million%20workplace%20injuries%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20over%205%2C000%20deaths%20as%20a%20result%20of%20workplace%20accidents%2C%20so%20any%20improvements%20would%20be%20significant.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20many%20of%20these%20working-class%20jobs%20may%20be%20physically%20or%20emotionally%20laborious%2C%20they%20are%20durable%20for%20the%20future.%20Broadly%20speaking%2C%20the%20jobs%20that%20will%20come%20out%20on%20top%20of%20the%20AI%20shuffle%20are%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aspeninstitute.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2016%2F04%2FRestore-the-Promise-of-Work-The-Aspen-Institute-2016.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egood-quality%20jobs%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20provide%20steady%20work%20hours%2C%20upward%20mobility%2C%20and%20career%20support%2C%20as%20well%20as%20%26quot%3Bfair%20compensation%20and%20a%20degree%20of%20voice%2C%26quot%3B%20Muro%20said.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20economy%20gets%20increasingly%20precarious%20because%20of%20AI%2C%20the%20winners%20of%20this%20AI%20revolution%20will%20not%20need%20to%20swim%20a%20technological%20triathlon%20against%20oncoming%20waves%20%E2%80%94%20they%20will%20already%20be%20on%20elevated%20terrain%2C%20safely%20and%20skillfully%20working%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20data-mrf-link%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Femil-skandul%5C%22%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-analytics-module%3D%5C%22body_link%5C%22%20data-analytics-post-depth%3D%5C%22100%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Femil-skandul%5C%22%20data-analytics-product-module%3D%5C%22body_link%5C%22%3EEmil%20Skandul%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0is%20a%20writer%20on%20technology%20and%20urban%20economics%2C%20and%20a%20Tony%20Blair%20Institute%20fellow.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjob-disruption-ai-future-careers-blue-collar-desk-work-2023-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698831422000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6539546b0487ff031cae35c4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjob-disruption-ai-future-careers-blue-collar-desk-work-2023-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Desk%20jobs%20are%20staring%20down%20decades%20of%20AI%20disruption.%20But%20careers%20like%20nursing%2C%20construction%2C%20and%20plumbing%20are%20booming%20%E2%80%94%20and%20safe%20from%20ChatGPT.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Emil%20Skandul)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjob-disruption-ai-future-careers-blue-collar-desk-work-2023-11%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22After%20Mouthwash%2C%20Pilots%20Now%20Directed%20To%20Not%20Use%20Tooth%20Gel%20Because...%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EPilots%20and%20crew%20members%20cannot%20use%20mouthwash%2C%20tooth%20gel%20or%20any%20such%20substance%20that%20has%20alcoholic%20content%2C%20as%20that%20could%20result%20in%20positive%20breath%20analyser%20test%2C%20according%20to%20revised%20norms%20issued%20by%20aviation%20regulator%20DGCA.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBesides%2C%20various%20changes%20have%20been%20made%20to%20the%20norms%20pertaining%20to%20the%20procedure%20for%20medical%20examination%20of%20aircraft%20personnel%20for%20alcohol%20consumption.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20release%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20DGCA%20said%20it%20has%20revised%20the%20Civil%20Aviation%20Requirements%20(CAR)%20on%20procedure%20for%20medical%20examination%20of%20aircraft%20personnel%20for%20alcohol%20consumption%20with%20the%20objective%20of%20enhancing%20safety%20of%20aircraft%20operations%20coupled%20with%20streamlining%20provisions%20of%20the%20existing%20regulations%20in%20line%20with%20feedback%20from%20industry%20and%20stakeholders%20from%20time%20to%20time%20for%20more%20effective%20implementation.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNo%20crew%20member%20shall%20consume%20any%20drug%2Fformulation%20or%20use%20any%20substance%20such%20as%20mouthwash%2Ftooth%20gel%20or%20any%20such%20product%20which%20has%20alcoholic%20content.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20may%20result%20into%20positive%20breath%20analyser%20test.%20Any%20crew%20member%20who%20is%20undergoing%20such%20medication%20shall%20consult%20the%20company%20doctor%20before%20undertaking%20flying%20assignment%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20per%20the%20DGCA.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20watchdog%2C%20in%20the%20draft%20CAR%2C%20had%20proposed%20barring%20crew%20from%20using%20any%20%26quot%3Bdrug%2Fformulation%20or%20use%20any%20substance%20such%20as%20mouthwash%2Ftooth%20gel%2Fperfume%20or%20any%20such%20product%20which%20has%20alcoholic%20content%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20word%20'perfume'%20is%20not%20included%20in%20the%20final%20CAR.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20Directorate%20General%20of%20Civil%20Aviation%20(DGCA)%2C%20breath%20analyser%20equipment%20with%20fuel%20cell%20technology%20has%20been%20made%20mandatory%20and%20a%20procedure%20for%20oversight%20and%20surveillance%20of%20calibration%20agencies%20has%20been%20introduced.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTo%20prevent%20missed%20breath%20analyser%20cases%2C%20a%20provision%20has%20been%20introduced%20wherein%20the%20operating%20crew%20travelling%20as%20passengers%20shall%20undergo%20breath%20analyser%20test%20at%20the%20boarding%20station%20in%20case%20of%20ramp%20to%20ramp%20transfer%20for%20operating%20flight%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20said%20in%20the%20CAR%20dated%20October%2030.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAmong%20other%20requirements%2C%20camera%20recording%20of%20breath%20analyser%20testing%20has%20been%20made%20mandatory%20for%20the%20operators%20engaged%20in%20seasonal%20pilgrimage%20operations%20and%20non-scheduled%20operators.%20Also%2C%20state%20governments%20should%20ensure%20the%20compliance%20of%20this%20requirement%20at%20base%20stations%20and%20in%20cases%20where%20they%20are%20away%20from%20base%20station%20for%20more%20than%20two%20days%20and%20operate%20a%20flight%20from%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20any%20crew%20member%2F%20student%20pilot%20after%20reaching%20the%20airport%20feels%20that%20he%2Fshe%20is%20unable%20to%20discharge%20his%20flying%20duties%20safely%20due%20to%20sickness%2C%20the%20crew%20member%20will%20intimate%20his%20company%20and%20in%20such%20case%20the%20breath-analyzer%20test%20shall%20not%20be%20conducted%20and%20the%20same%20will%20not%20be%20considered%20as%20missed%20BA.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHowever%2C%20the%20crew%20member%2F%20student%20pilot%20shall%20not%20be%20rostered%20for%20flying%20duties%20on%20that%20day%20and%20subsequently%20shall%20be%20rostered%20for%20flying%20duties%20after%20review%20by%20the%20company%20doctor%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20release%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETo%20facilitate%20the%20operators%20specially%20in%20general%20aviation%2C%20the%20regulator%20has%20enhanced%20the%20scope%20of%20facilities%20for%20undergoing%20the%20breath%20analyser%20examination.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EUnder%20the%20DGCA%20norms%2C%20for%20all%20scheduled%20operators%2C%20each%20flight%20crew%20member%20and%20cabin%20crew%20member%20shall%20be%20subjected%20to%20pre-flight%20breath%20analyser%20examination%20at%20first%20departure%20airport%20during%20a%20flight%20duty%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFor%20all%20scheduled%20flights%20originating%20from%20destinations%20outside%20India%2C%20post-flight%20breath%20analyser%20examination%20of%20each%20flight%20crew%20and%20cabin%20crew%20shall%20be%20carried%20out%20at%20the%20first%20port%20of%20landing%20in%20India%2C%20as%20per%20the%20norms.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EStringent%20punishments%20are%20in%20place%20when%20a%20crew%20tests%20positive%20in%20a%20breath%20analyser%20test%2C%20depending%20on%20whether%20it%20is%20repetitive.%20It%20is%20applicable%20for%20both%20pre%20and%20post%20flight%20tests.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698831420000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-03%2F1r4gusu8_pilot-generic_625x300_25_March_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fafter-mouthwash-pilots-now-directed-to-not-use-tooth-gel-because-4534714%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Various%20changes%20have%20been%20made%20to%20the%20norms%20pertaining%20to%20the%20procedure%20for%20medical%20examination%20of%20aircraft%20personnel%20for%20alcoh