i%3EA%20business%20analyst%20at%20Amazon%20was%20laid%20off%20as%20part%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-laying-off-17000-workers-largest-job-cut-tech-report-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejob%20cuts%20in%20January%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAbout%20a%20month%20later%2C%20the%20worker%20got%20the%20first%20of%20four%20inquiries%20about%20going%20back%20to%20the%20company.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%26quot%3BI%20didn't%20want%20to%20go%20back%20because%20I%20just%20lost%20trust%20in%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20worker%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20a%20former%20Amazon%20business%20analyst%20laid%20off%20in%20January%20as%20part%20of%20job%20cuts%20that%20hit%2018%2C000%20workers.%20Though%20this%20person%20was%20granted%20anonymity%2C%20their%20identity%20is%20known%20to%20Insider.%20The%20conversation%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20very%20quiet%20for%20most%20of%20the%20morning.%20We%20were%20made%20aware%20that%20we%20would%20be%20getting%20an%20email%20if%20we%20were%20getting%20laid%20off.%20I%20was%20working%20remotely%20and%20a%20couple%20of%20us%20were%20just%20setting%20up%20meetings%20and%20chatting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20hard%20to%20get%20any%20work%20done.%20I%20was%20just%20talking%20to%20friends%20occasionally.%20I%20was%20also%20obsessively%20refreshing%20my%20email.%20Even%20that%20morning%2C%20I%20was%20applying%20for%20some%20jobs%20because%20I%20had%20a%20feeling%20that%20something%20could%20happen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20I%20got%20the%20email%20between%2011%20a.m.%20and%20noon.%20It%20said%20something%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BAs%20you%20know%2C%20we're%20doing%20a%20reorg%20and%20unfortunately%20your%20role%20has%20been%20made%20redundant%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20or%20something%20like%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20got%20the%20email%2C%20I%20remember%20messaging%20my%20friend.%20Then%20she%20called%20me%20and%20I%20realized%20that%20her%20manager%2C%20who%20was%20trying%20to%20save%20people%2C%20also%20got%20laid%20off.%20She%20was%20blindsided%20by%20it.%20People%20were%20crying.%20They%20were%20traveling%20for%20work%20so%20that%20made%20it%20worse.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20very%20shocking%20because%20you're%20working%2C%20you%20have%20a%20job%2C%20and%20then%20immediately%20it's%2C%20%26quot%3BOK%2C%20we're%20just%20going%20to%20pay%20you%20for%20the%20next%20two%20months%2C%20and%20we%20expect%20you%20to%20do%20nothing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20hadn't%20been%20there%20super%20long%20%E2%80%94%20about%20a%20year.%20But%20I%20really%20enjoyed%20the%20role%20for%20a%20while%20there.%20And%20I%20really%20enjoyed%20my%20manager%2C%20too.%20But%20then%20it%20started%20getting%20a%20little%20bit%20weird%20where%20we%20knew%20there%20was%20something%20coming.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20so%20it%20got%20to%20be%20an%20every-man-for-himself%20situation%20pretty%20quick%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0people%20trying%20to%20make%20themselves%20look%20good%2C%20people%20jumping%20ship%20before%20it%20actually%20came%20to%20bear.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20whole%20situation%20felt%20out%20of%20control%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20the%20layoffs%2C%20I%20was%20talking%20to%20my%20manager%20who%20said%20I%20didn't%20have%20anything%20to%20worry%20about.%20My%20manager%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BThere's%20not%20anybody%20else%20on%20the%20team%20who%20does%20what%20you%20do.%20So%20you%20don't%20need%20to%20be%20concerned.%26quot%3B%20It%20turns%20out%20that%20wasn't%20the%20case.%20The%20direct%20managers%20had%20nothing%20to%20do%20with%20the%20layoff%20decisions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20a%20point%20a%20month%20or%20two%20before%20the%20layoffs%20where%20we%20were%20asked%20to%20fill%20out%20a%20document%20where%20we%20were%20to%20write%20things%20that%20we%20had%20worked%20on%2C%20things%20that%20we%20owned%2C%20and%20projects%20that%20we%20were%20looking%20to%20complete%20in%20the%20upcoming%20year.%20It%20was%20a%20shared%20doc%20so%20everyone%20could%20edit%20it.%20So%20people%20were%20editing%20other%20people's%20things%20and%20it%20was%20kind%20of%20a%20mess.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20people%20I%20was%20working%20with%20were%20putting%20their%20names%20on%20my%20technical%20pieces.%20And%20so%20it%20kind%20of%20looked%20like%20I%20was%20just%20tagging%20on%20to%20these%20projects%20when%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20I%20was%20owning%20those%20projects.%20Some%20of%20the%20people%20who%20added%20their%20names%20to%20my%20projects%20presented%20it%20to%20me%20as%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BOh%2C%20hey%2C%20I%20added%20my%20name%20to%20some%20of%20your%20things%20because%20we're%20working%20closely%20together%20on%20it.%26quot%3B%20I%20was%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BOK%2C%20that's%20fine.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20hindsight%2C%20I%20wish%20I%20had%20gone%20back%20and%20pushed%20to%20have%20their%20names%20taken%20off.%20But%20I%20just%20felt%20at%20the%20time%20that%20that%20would%20be%20petty%20and%20I%20didn't%20want%20to%20get%20into%20those%20discussions%20because%20my%20name%20was%20still%20on%20the%20items.%20I%20felt%20like%20the%20whole%20situation%20was%20sort%20of%20out%20of%20control.%20And%20at%20that%20point%2C%20I%20was%20like%2C%20alright%2C%20I%20guess%20we'll%20just%20kind%20of%20go%20with%20the%20flow.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EManagement%20was%20saying%20this%20document%20was%20not%20a%20cause%20for%20concern.%20They%20said%20they%20were%20asking%20for%20the%20information%20because%20we%20had%20some%20newer%20leaders%20who%20wanted%20to%20get%20a%20better%20lay%20of%20the%20land.%20But%20we%20were%20concerned%20nevertheless.%20It%20didn't%20really%20help%20to%20fill%20in%20the%20trust%20that%20was%20missing%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20actually%20had%20to%20do%20the%20document%20twice%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0once%20before%20the%20November%20wave%20of%20layoffs%20and%20then%20we%20got%20a%20second%20push%20for%20it%20near%20the%20time%20when%20I%20got%20laid%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20were%20worried%20in%20November%20because%20we%20got%20very%20little%20information%20when%20that%20first%20round%20of%20layoffs%20happened.%20We%20were%20traveling%20for%20work%20and%20we%20were%20worried%20that%20we%20were%20gonna%20get%20laid%20off%20while%20we%20were%20on%20the%20road.%20We'd%20been%20concerned%20about%20layoffs%2C%20especially%20when%20we%20saw%20that%20our%20managers%20were%20leaving.%20Even%20though%20they%20gave%20us%20reasons%20as%20to%20why%20they%20were%20leaving%2C%20we%20basically%20understood%20what%20was%20happening.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20applied%20to%20close%20to%20200%20jobs%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20I%20got%20laid%20off%2C%20I%20just%20hit%20the%20ground%20running%20the%20next%20day%20applying%20for%20jobs.%20I%20had%20my%20Amazon%20computer%20closed%20and%20waited%20for%20them%20to%20send%20me%20a%20box%20to%20ship%20that%20and%20the%20rest%20of%20my%20equipment%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20were%20saying%20you%20can%20look%20for%20opportunities%20within%20Amazon%20if%20you%20want.%20And%20I%20was%20like%20absolutely%20not.%20I%20just%20felt%20so%20unappreciated.%20I%20consider%20myself%20a%20high-performer%20on%20the%20team.%20My%20manager%20and%20then%20their%20manager%20were%20always%20telling%20me%20that%20I%20was%20someone%20they%20wanted%20to%20protect%20and%20that%20I%20was%20someone%20they%20valued%20a%20lot.%20And%20at%20the%20end%2C%20it%20really%20didn't%20feel%20that%20way%20at%20all.%20It%20felt%20really%20depersonalized%20and%20almost%20just%20like%20a%20slap%20across%20the%20face%20because%20you%20give%20so%20much%20to%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20probably%20applied%20to%20close%20to%20200%20jobs.%20The%20market%20was%20really%20rough%20because%20there%20were%20so%20many%20tech%20layoffs%20right%20in%20a%20row%20and%20everyone%20was%20getting%20scared.%20So%20it%20was%20really%20hard%20to%20find%20anything.%20We%20had%20two%20months'%20severance%20and%20then%20we'd%20get%20a%20payout%20at%20the%20end%20of%20that%20time%20that's%20relative%20to%20your%20tenure%20at%20Amazon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGiven%20that%20it's%20kind%20of%20a%20high-skill%20job%20and%20you%20have%20to%20go%20through%20a%20lot%20of%20interviews%2C%20it%20was%20rough.%20I%20definitely%20went%20through%20a%20lot%20of%20anxiety%20and%20filled%20out%20a%20lot%20of%20applications%20because%20of%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20all%20those%20applications%2C%20about%2010%20to%2015%20turned%20into%20interviews%20if%20you're%20including%20phone%20screenings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EAmazon%20comes%20calling%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20got%20my%20first%20outreach%20on%20LinkedIn%20on%20behalf%20of%20Amazon%20a%20little%20over%20a%20month%20after%20they%20told%20us%20we%20were%20getting%20laid%20off.%20It%20was%20still%20within%20the%20period%20where%20we%20had%20our%20severance%20payments.%20The%20message%20was%20from%20an%20external%20recruiter%20that%20Amazon%20worked%20with.%20I%20told%20them%20I'm%20not%20interested.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbout%2010%20days%20later%2C%20my%20former%20manager%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0the%20one%20who'd%20moved%20to%20another%20division%20before%20the%20layoffs%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0reached%20out.%20He%20was%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BThere's%20someone%20on%20my%20new%20team%20who's%20opening%20up%20a%20new%20role.%20I%20totally%20understand%20if%20you're%20done%20with%20Amazon%20at%20this%20point.%20But%20is%20that%20something%20you'd%20be%20interested%20in%3F%26quot%3B%20And%20I%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BNo%2C%20I'm%20good.%20Thank%20you.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20still%20didn't%20have%20a%20job%20at%20that%20point%20but%20I%20just%20couldn't%20imagine%20going%20back%20if%20I%20didn't%20have%20to.%20There%20are%20people%20who%20got%20laid%20off%20with%20me%20who've%20gone%20back.%20One%20is%20consulting%20for%20Amazon%20right%20now%20because%20he%20kind%20of%20got%20forced%20to.%20And%20another%20one%20accepted%20a%20role%20for%20like%20a%20month%20or%20two%20before%20she%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BYou%20know%2C%20I%20found%20something%20better.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20thing%20that%20rubbed%20me%20the%20wrong%20way%20was%20that%20they%20clearly%20had%20roles%20for%20these%20people.%20You're%20hiring%20for%20the%20same%20job%20that%20I%20had.%20But%20yet%20you're%20telling%20me%20my%20role%20is%20redundant.%20I'm%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BWhich%20one%20is%20it%3F%26quot%3B%20Because%20now%2C%20you've%20reached%20out%20to%20me%20more%20than%20once%20for%20almost%20exactly%20the%20same%20job%20that%20I%20was%20just%20doing.%20You%20should%20be%20having%20a%20hiring%20freeze%20right%20now.%20And%20you%20should%20be%20trying%20to%20reorg%20internally%20because%20the%20whole%20message%20was%2C%20%26quot%3BWe%20have%20too%20many%20people%20and%20we've%20over-hired.%26quot%3B%20So%20why%20are%20you%20still%20hiring%20them%3F%20Like%20to%20the%20point%20where%20there's%20a%20need%20for%20three%20of%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20would%20later%20find%20out%20by%20talking%20to%20the%20third%20person%20who%20reached%20out%20to%20me%20%E2%80%94%20a%20recruiter%20%E2%80%94%20that%20some%20companies%20tell%20them%20to%20go%20for%20people%20who%20used%20to%20work%20for%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EIt's%20like%20you're%20getting%20covered%20in%20ants%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20feel%20like%20a%20lot%20of%20it%20was%20sort%20of%20playing%20with%20people's%20livelihoods%20and%20mental%20health%20and%20safety%20for%20the%20sake%20of%2C%20I%20would%20say%2C%20an%20almost%20arbitrary%20layoff%20process%20%E2%80%94%20just%20to%20kind%20of%20look%20like%20you're%20doing%20something.%20It%20seemed%20very%20artificial%20to%20me.%20It%20kind%20of%20seemed%20like%20you're%20getting%20covered%20in%20ants%20and%20you're%20getting%20overwhelmed.%20Then%20you%20shake%20a%20bunch%20off%20but%20you%20let%20the%20ants%20keep%20crawling%20up%20you%20and%20it's%20just%20sort%20of%20fruitless.%20Like%2C%20%26quot%3BWhat%20are%20you%20doing%3F%26quot%3B%20If%20you%20don't%20make%20a%20structural%20change%20to%20address%20the%20over-hiring%20then%20it's%20going%20to%20keep%20kind%20of%20growing%20like%20a%20cancer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20didn't%20want%20to%20go%20back%20because%20I%20just%20lost%20trust%20in%20them.%20I%20did%20feel%20like%20it%20could%20easily%20happen%20again%20because%20I%20was%20in%20a%20position%20where%20I%20felt%20like%20I%20was%20doing%20a%20really%20good%20job%20and%20I%20was%20working%20hard.%20And%20I%20was%20really%20motivated%20in%20the%20beginning.%20I%20felt%20that%20none%20of%20that%20really%20mattered%20to%20them%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20guess%20I'm%20somebody%20who%20%E2%80%94%20I%20guess%20most%20people%20are%20like%20this%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0where%20if%20you%20don't%20see%20the%20fruits%20of%20your%20labor%2C%20it's%20kind%20of%20demotivating%20to%20have%20that%20kind%20of%20response%20to%20your%20hard%20work.%20But%20also%2C%20the%20trust%20factor%20was%20huge.%20Because%20I%20felt%20like%20there%20was%20nothing%20I%20could%20do%20that%20would%20really%20give%20me%20any%20kind%20of%20security%20there.%20Especially%20given%20that%20I%20couldn't%20really%20understand%20why%20they%20were%20doing%20what%20they%20were%20doing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20last%20month%2C%20I%20got%20another%20email%20about%20being%20an%20Amazon%20boomeranger%2C%20where%20you%20can%20come%20back%20within%20a%20certain%20amount%20of%20time%20without%20completing%20a%20full%20interview%20process.%20It%20was%20the%20fourth%20inquiry%20about%20coming%20back%20I'd%20gotten.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20pressure%20when%20I%20first%20got%20reached%20out%20to%20about%20going%20back%20to%20Amazon.%20But%20the%20visceral%20response%20was%20just%20so%20intense%20that%20I%20was%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20can't%20do%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAugust%20Aldebot-Green%2C%20an%20Amazon%20spokesperson%2C%20told