utional%20Bench%20looking%20into%20pleas%20against%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme%2C%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20October%2031%2C%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CSuppose%20%E2%80%98A%E2%80%99%2C%20a%20person%2C%20purchases%20electoral%20bonds%20worth%20Rs%20100%20crore.%20%E2%80%98A%E2%80%99%20is%20only%20put%20up%20by%20%E2%80%98B%E2%80%99%20for%20the%20purchase%20as%20he%20has%20a%20%5Bverified%20or%20know-your-customer%5D%20KYC%20account.%20It%20is%20%E2%80%98B%E2%80%99%20who%20actually%20gives%20the%20donation%20to%20the%20political%20party%E2%80%A6%20%E2%80%98B%E2%80%99%20can%20also%20be%20an%20aggregator%20of%20electoral%20bonds%20by%20having%20100%20people%20buy%20bonds%20worth%20Rs%201%20crore%20each.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20on%20Tuesday%20began%20specifically%20hearing%20four%20petitions%20moved%20by%20the%20Association%20for%20Democratic%20Reforms%2C%20Communist%20Party%20of%20India%20(Marxist)%2C%20Congress%20leader%20Jaya%20Thakur%2C%20and%20public%20interest%20litigation%20by%20one%20Spandan%20Biswal.%20The%20petitioners%20urged%20the%20court%20to%20declare%20political%20parties%20as%20public%20offices%20to%20bring%20them%20under%20the%20ambit%20of%20the%20Right%20to%20Information%20Act%20(RTI%20Act)%20and%20to%20compel%20them%20to%20disclose%20their%20income%20and%20expenditure.%20They%20also%20challenged%20the%20constitutional%20validity%20of%20the%20scheme.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20observed%20that%20anonymity%20for%20political%20donations%20under%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme%20perhaps%20could%20be%20aimed%20at%20preventing%20repercussions%20from%20parties%20to%20which%20a%20person%20or%20entity%20has%20not%20donated.%20%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20also%20an%20assumption%20that%20if%20you%20disclose%20the%20name%20of%20the%20donor%2C%20there%20will%20be%20other%20political%20parties%20who%20will%20know%20that%20you%20have%20contributed%20to%20one%20particular%20party%E2%80%A6%20Suppose%20you%20are%20contributing%20to%20a%20party%20not%20in%20power%E2%80%A6%20suppose%20the%20donor%20is%20carrying%20on%20business%20in%20the%20state%20and%20his%20name%20is%20made%20available%20to%20all%E2%80%A6%20There%20is%20logic%20there%3B%20whether%20it%20is%20valid%20or%20not%2C%20we%20have%20to%20decide%2C%E2%80%9D%20CJI%20Chandrachud%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Kapil%20Sibal%2C%20counsel%20for%20one%20of%20the%20petitioners%2C%20said%20in%20%E2%80%9Cpractical%20politics%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20donor%20would%20inform%20the%20political%20party%20about%20his%20donation.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAnother%20counsel%20Shadan%20Farasat%20said%20the%20scheme%20set%20up%20a%20%E2%80%9Clegally%20directed%20informational%20blackhole%E2%80%9D%20which%20could%20skew%20the%20electoral%20playing%20field.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20scheme%20is%20not%20meant%20to%20reduce%20the%20black%20money%20funding%20of%20political%20parties%2C%20but%20to%20re-route%20the%20non-anonymous%20banking%20channel%20funding%20to%20anonymous%20electoral%20bonds.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPrashant%20Bhushan%2C%20the%20lawyer%20for%20another%20petitioner%2C%20said%20that%20it%20is%20a%20fundamental%20right%20of%20a%20citizen%20to%20know%20the%20funding%20of%20political%20parties.%20Calling%20electoral%20bonds%20%E2%80%9Clegalised%20kickbacks%E2%80%9D%2C%20he%20said%20the%20system%20can%20destroy%20democracy%20and%20tilt%20the%20level%20playing%20field%20during%20elections.%20He%20then%20went%20on%20to%20say%20that%20over%2090%25%20of%20the%20donations%20go%20to%20ruling%20parties.%20Therefore%2C%20he%20said%20they%20are%20meant%20for%20favours%20done%20or%20anticipated.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20Union%20government%20in%20its%20submission%20to%20the%20court%20said%20that%20citizens%E2%80%99%20right%20to%20know%20is%20subject%20to%20reasonable%20restrictions.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fexplained%2Fexplained-law%2Fsc-electoral-bonds-hearing-explained-9006289%2F%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20the%20%3Cem%3EIndian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Attorney%20General%20R.%20Venkataramani%20stated%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthere%20can%20be%20no%20general%20right%20to%20know%20anything%E2%80%9D%20without%20%E2%80%9Creasonable%20restrictions%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698829250000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F03%2F09172044%2FScreen-Shot-2021-03-09-at-5.20.25-PM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Felectoral-bonds-sc-raises-concern-over-possible-quid-pro-quo-favours-between-ruling-parties-donors%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20five-judge%20constitutional%20bench%2C%20headed%20by%20Chief%20Justice%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%2C%20began%20hearing%20pleas%20on%20Tuesday%20challenging%20the%20constitutional%20validity%20of%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Felectoral-bonds-sc-raises-concern-over-possible-quid-pro-quo-favours-between-ruling-parties-donors%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Vikram%20plays%20a%20violent%20and%20greedy%20man%20in%20'Thangalaan'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698829209000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-104884549%2Cimgsize-700378.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Ftamil%2Fmovies%2Fnews%2Fvikram-plays-a-violent-and-greedy-man-in-thangalaan-watch-the-teaser-here%2Farticleshow%2F104883625.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%26quot%3BThangalaan%26quot%3B%2C%20directed%20by%20Pa%20Ranjith%20and%20starring%20Vikram%20in%20the%20lead%20role%2C%20had%20its%20teaser%20launched%20in%20Chennai.%20The%20film%20is%20an%20action%20drama%20where%20Vikram%20plays%20the%20titular%20role%20of%20the%20%26quot%3Bson%20of%20gold%26quot%3B.%20The%20teaser%20showcases%20Vikram%20in%20intense%20and%20violent%20scenes%2C%20hinting%20at%20a%20story%20of%20blood%2C