09785%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EOctober%2031%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20decided%20in%20the%20Cabinet%20meeting%20to%20send%20reinforcements%20to%20Moreh%2C%20which%20also%20came%20under%20attack%2C%20injuring%20three%20policemen%20seriously.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThree%20commandos%20%E2%80%93%20S.%20Thuikhavang%2C%20S.%20Sekharjit%2C%20and%20L.%20Bangkim%20Singh%20%E2%80%93%20sustained%20bullet%20injuries%20and%20were%20airlifted%20to%20Raj%20Medicity%20Hospital%20for%20treatment.%20The%20police%20convoy%20was%20attacked%20at%20two%20different%20locations%20on%20the%20Indo-Mynamar%20national%20highway%20whilst%20it%20was%20on%20its%20way%20to%20Moreh.%20They%20were%20first%20ambushed%20at%20Bongyang%20village%2C%20but%20the%20police%20did%20not%20retaliate%20and%20continued%20their%20journey%20to%20Moreh.%20The%20second%20ambush%20took%20place%20at%20K%20Sinam%20village%2C%20where%20an%20exchange%20of%20fire%20took%20place%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiatoday.in%2Findia%2Fstory%2F3-cops-injured-manipur-police-team-reinforcement-moreh-ambushed-2456352-2023-10-31%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20%3Cem%3EIndia%20Today%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Manipur%20government%2C%20in%20a%20statement%20after%20the%20cabinet%20meeting%2C%20said%20a%20first%20information%20report%20(FIR)%20has%20been%20filed%20against%20an%20organisation%20called%20%E2%80%98World%20Kuki-Zo%20Intellectual%20Council%E2%80%99%2C%20which%20had%20issued%20a%20statement%20on%20October%2024%20asking%20%E2%80%9Cvolunteers%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20Kuki-Zo%20community%20to%20take%20up%20arms.%20It%20had%20said%20the%20Kuki%20National%20Army%20and%20other%20insurgent%20groups%20could%20not%20%E2%80%9Cjoin%20the%20war%E2%80%9D%20due%20to%20the%20tripartite%20suspension%20of%20operations%20(SoO)%20agreement%20with%20the%20Union%20and%20the%20state%20governments.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20the%20SoO%20agreement%2C%20at