ated%20Oct.%2013%2C%202023%2C%20bears%20the%20logo%20of%20the%20Intelligence%20Ministry%20%E2%80%94%20a%20small%20governmental%20body%20that%20produces%20policy%20research%20and%20shares%20its%20proposals%20with%20intelligence%20agencies%2C%20the%20army%2C%20and%20other%20ministries.%20It%20assesses%20three%20options%20regarding%20the%20future%20of%20the%20Palestinians%20in%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%20in%20the%20framework%20of%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.972mag.com%2Ftopic%2Foctober-2023-war%2F%5C%22%3Ecurrent%20war%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20recommends%20a%20full%20population%20transfer%20as%20its%20preferred%20course%20of%20action.%20It%20also%20calls%20on%20Israel%20to%20enlist%20the%20international%20community%20in%20support%20of%20this%20endeavor.%20The%20document%2C%20whose%20authenticity%20was%20confirmed%20by%20the%20ministry%2C%20has%20been%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scribd.com%2Fdocument%2F681086738%2FIsraeli-Intelligence-Ministry-Policy-Paper-on-Gaza-s-Civilian-Population-October-2023%5C%22%3Etranslated%20into%20English%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0in%20full%20here%20on%20%2B972.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20existence%20of%20the%20document%20does%20not%20necessarily%20indicate%20that%20its%20recommendations%20are%20being%20considered%20by%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20defense%20establishment.%20Despite%20its%20name%2C%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gov.il%2Fen%2Fdepartments%2Fministry-of-intelligence%2Fgovil-landing-page%5C%22%3EIntelligence%20Ministry%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20not%20directly%20responsible%20for%20any%20intelligence%20body%2C%20but%20rather%20independently%20prepares%20studies%20and%20policy%20papers%20that%20are%20distributed%20to%20the%20Israeli%20government%20and%20security%20agencies%20for%20review%2C%20but%20are%20not%20binding.%20The%20ministry%E2%80%99s%20annual%20budget%20is%20NIS%2025%20million%20and%20its%20influence%20is%20considered%20relatively%20small.%20It%20is%20currently%20headed%20by%20Gila%20Gamliel%2C%20a%20member%20of%20Prime%20Minister%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu%E2%80%99s%20Likud%20Party.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20fact%20that%20an%20Israeli%20government%20ministry%20has%20prepared%20such%20a%20detailed%20proposal%20amid%20a%20large-scale%20military%20offensive%20on%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%2C%20following%20Hamas%E2%80%99%20deadly%20assault%20and%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.972mag.com%2Fmassacre-israel-south-gaza-war%2F%5C%22%3Emassacres%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0in%20southern%20Israeli%20communities%20on%20Oct.%207%2C%20reflects%20how%20the%20idea%20of%20forced%20population%20transfer%20is%20being%20raised%20to%20the%20level%20of%20official%20policy%20discussions.%20Fears%20of%20such%20plans%20%E2%80%94%20which%20would%20constitute%20a%20serious%20war%20crime%20under%20international%20law%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.972mag.com%2Fgaza-nakba-sinai-egypt-israel%2F%5C%22%3Ehave%20grown%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0in%20recent%20weeks%2C%20especially%20after%20the%20Israeli%20army%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.972mag.com%2Fnorth-gaza-stay-or-leave-invasion%2F%5C%22%3Eordered%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0about%201%20million%20Palestinians%20to%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.972mag.com%2Fgaza-salah-al-din-road%2F%5C%22%3Eevacuate%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0the%20northern%20Gaza%20Strip%20ahead%20of%20escalating%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.972mag.com%2Fjabalia-camp-ghost-town-gaza-war%2F%5C%22%3Ebombardment%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0and%20incremental%20ground%20incursions.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20document%20recommends%20that%20Israel%20act%20to%20%E2%80%9Cevacuate%20the%20civilian%20population%20to%20Sinai%E2%80%9D%20during%20the%20war%3B%20establish%20tent%20cities%20and%20later%20more%20permanent%20cities%20in%20the%20northern%20Sinai%20that%20will%20absorb%20the%20expelled%20population%3B%20and%20then%20create%20%E2%80%9Ca%20sterile%20zone%20of%20several%20kilometers%20%E2%80%A6%20within%20Egypt%2C%20and%20%5Bprevent%5D%20the%20return%20of%20the%20population%20to%20activities%2Fresidences%20near%20the%20border%20with%20Israel.%E2%80%9D%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20governments%20around%20the%20world%2C%20led%20by%20the%20United%20States%2C%20must%20be%20mobilized%20to%20implement%20the%20move.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20source%20in%20the%20Intelligence%20Ministry%20confirmed%20to%20Local%20Call%2F%2B972%20that%20the%20document%20was%20authentic%2C%20that%20it%20was%20distributed%20to%20the%20defense%20establishment%20by%20the%20ministry%E2%80%99s%20policy%20division%2C%20and%20%E2%80%9Cwas%20not%20supposed%20to%20reach%20the%20media.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3E%E2%80%98Make%20it%20clear%20there%20is%20no%20hope%20of%20returning%E2%80%99%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20document%20unequivocally%20and%20explicitly%20recommends%20transferring%20Palestinian%20civilians%20from%20Gaza%20as%20the%20desired%20outcome%20of%20the%20war.%20The%20existence%20of%20the%20plan%20was%20first%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.calcalist.co.il%2Flocal_news%2Farticle%2Frj2mplngp%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0last%20week%20in%20the%20Israeli%20business%20newspaper%20Calcalist%2C%20and%20the%20full%20text%20of%20the%20document%20is%20published%20and%20translated%20here.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20transfer%20plan%20is%20divided%20into%20several%20stages.%20In%20the%20first%20stage%2C%20action%20must%20be%20taken%20so%20that%20the%20population%20of%20Gaza%20%E2%80%9Cevacuates%20south%2C%E2%80%9D%20while%20the%20air%20strikes%20focus%20on%20the%20northern%20Gaza%20Strip.%20In%20the%20second%20stage%2C%20a%20ground%20incursion%20into%20Gaza%20will%20begin%2C%20leading%20to%20the%20occupation%20of%20the%20entire%20Strip%20from%20north%20to%20south%2C%20and%20the%20%E2%80%9Ccleansing%20of%20the%20underground%20bunkers%20of%20Hamas%20fighters.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EConcurrently%20with%20the%20re-occupation%20of%20Gaza%2C%20Palestinian%20civilians%20will%20be%20moved%20into%20Egyptian%20territory%2C%20and%20not%20be%20allowed%20to%20return.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20important%20to%20leave%20the%20travel%20routes%20to%20the%20south%20open%20to%20enable%20the%20evacuation%20of%20the%20civilian%20population%20toward%20Rafah%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20document%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20an%20official%20in%20the%20Intelligence%20Ministry%2C%20the%20ministry%E2%80%99s%20personnel%20stand%20behind%20these%20recommendations.%20The%20source%20stressed%20that%20the%20ministry%E2%80%99s%20research%20is%20%E2%80%9Cnot%20based%20on%20military%20intelligence%E2%80%9D%20and%20serves%20only%20as%20a%20basis%20for%20discussions%20within%20the%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20document%20proposes%20promoting%20a%20campaign%20targeting%20Palestinian%20civilians%20in%20Gaza%20that%20will%20%E2%80%9Cmotivate%20them%20to%20accept%20this%20plan%E2%80%9D%20and%20lead%20them%20to%20give%20up%20their%20land.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20messages%20should%20revolve%20around%20the%20loss%20of%20land%2C%20making%20it%20clear%20that%20there%20is%20no%20hope%20of%20returning%20to%20the%20territories%20Israel%20will%20soon%20occupy%2C%20whether%20or%20not%20that%20is%20true.%20The%20image%20needs%20to%20be%2C%20%E2%80%98Allah%20made%20sure%20you%20lose%20this%20land%20because%20of%20Hamas%E2%80%99%20leadership%20%E2%80%94%20there%20is%20no%20choice%20but%20to%20move%20to%20another%20place%20with%20the%20assistance%20of%20your%20Muslim%20brothers%2C%E2%80%99%E2%80%9D%20the%20document%20reads.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scribd.com%2Fembeds%2F681086738%2Fcontent%5C%22%20data-mce-fragment%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22980%5C%22%20data-aspect-ratio%3D%5C%220.7080062794348508%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Israeli%20Intelligence%20Ministry%20Policy%20Paper%20on%20Gaza%E2%80%99s%20Civilian%20Population%2C%20October%202023%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%2C%20the%20document%20encourages%20the%20government%20to%20lead%20a%20public%20campaign%20in%20the%20Western%20world%20to%20promote%20the%20transfer%20plan%20%E2%80%9Cin%20a%20way%20that%20does%20not%20incite%20or%20vilify%20Israel.%E2%80%9D%20This%20would%20be%20done%20by%20presenting%20the%20expulsion%20of%20Gaza%E2%80%99s%20population%20as%20a%20humanitarian%20necessity%20to%20win%20over%20international%20support%2C%20by%20arguing%20that%20relocation%20will%20lead%20to%20%E2%80%9Cfewer%20casualties%20among%20the%20civilian%20population%20compared%20to%20the%20expected%20casualties%20if%20the%20population%20remains.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20document%20also%20says%20that%20the%20United%20States%20should%20be%20enlisted%20in%20the%20process%20to%20exert%20pressure%20on%20Egypt%20to%20absorb%20the%20Palestinian%20residents%20of%20Gaza%2C%20and%20that%20other%20European%20countries%20%E2%80%93%20particularly%20Greece%20and%20Spain%20%E2%80%93%20as%20well%20as%20Canada%20should%20help%20absorb%20and%20settle%20the%20Palestinian%20refugees.%20The%20Ministry%20of%20Intelligence%20said%20the%20document%20was%20not%20yet%20formally%20distributed%20to%20U.S.%20officials%2C%20but%20only%20to%20the%20Israeli%20government%20and%20security%20agencies.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EA%20wider%20policy%20discussion%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ELast%20week%2C%20the%20Misgav%20Institute%2C%20a%20right-wing%20think%20tank%20headed%20by%20Meir%20Ben-Shabbat%2C%20a%20close%20associate%20of%20Prime%20Minister%20Netanyahu%20and%20a%20former%20head%20of%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20National%20Security%20Council%2C%20published%20a%20position%20paper%20that%20similarly%20called%20for%20the%20forced%20transfer%20of%20Gaza%E2%80%99s%20population%20to%20the%20Sinai.%20The%20institute%20recently%20deleted%20the%20post%20from%20Twitter%20and%20from%20its%20website%20after%20drawing%20strong%20international%20censure.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20deleted%20study%20was%20written%20by%20Amir%20Weitmann%2C%20a%20Likud%20activist%20and%2C%20according%20to%20sources%20familiar%20with%20him%2C%20a%20close%20associate%20of%20Intelligence%20Minister%20Gila%20Gamliel.%20Last%20week%2C%20on%20a%20Facebook%20page%20named%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Plan%20to%20Rehabilitate%20Gaza%20in%20Egypt%2C%E2%80%9D%20Weitmann%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.facebook.com%2Fwatch%2F%3Fv%3D6498832673572815%5C%22%3Einterviewed%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0Likud%20MK%20Ariel%20Kallner%2C%20who%20told%20him%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20solution%20you%20propose%2C%20to%20move%20the%20population%20to%20Egypt%2C%20is%20a%20logical%20and%20necessary%20solution.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20not%20the%20only%20connection%20between%20the%20Likud%2C%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Intelligence%2C%20and%20the%20right-wing%20think%20tank.%20About%20a%20month%20ago%2C%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Intelligence%20pledged%20to%20transfer%20about%20NIS%201%20million%20from%20its%20budget%20to%20the%20Misgav%20Institute%20to%20conduct%20research%20on%20Arab%20countries.%20If%20the%20Misgav%20Institute%20was%20somehow%20involved%20in%20drafting%20the%20ministry%E2%80%99s%20Gaza%20transfer%20recommendations%2C%20its%20logo%2C%20at%20least%2C%20does%20not%20appear%20on%20the%20document.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESources%20in%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Intelligence%20said%20that%20the%20Gaza%20report%20was%20an%20independent%20study%20conducted%20by%20the%20ministry%E2%80%99s%20policy%20division%2C%20without%20the%20cooperation%20of%20an%20external%20party%2C%20but%20they%20did%20confirm%20that%20the%20ministry%20had%20recently%20begun%20working%20with%20the%20Misgav%20Institute%2C%20stressing%20that%20the%20government%20body%20works%20with%20various%20research%20groups%20with%20diverse%20political%20agendas.%20The%20Misgav%20Institute%20has%20not%20yet%20responded%20to%20queries%20for%20this%20article.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%2C%20the%20Intelligence%20Ministry%E2%80%99s%20document%20was%20first%20leaked%20in%20a%20small%20internal%20WhatsApp%20group%20of%20right-wing%20activists%20who%2C%20together%20with%20Likud%20advocate%20Whiteman%2C%20promote%20the%20reestablishment%20of%20Israeli%20settlements%20in%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%20and%20the%20transfer%20of%20Palestinians%20living%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20one%20of%20these%20activists%2C%20the%20Intelligence%20Ministry%20document%20reached%20them%20through%20the%20mediation%20of%20a%20%E2%80%9CLikud%20source%2C%E2%80%9D%20and%20its%20public%20distribution%20is%20related%20to%20an%20attempt%20to%20find%20out%20whether%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20Israeli%20public%20is%20ready%20to%20accept%20ideas%20of%20transfer%20from%20Gaza.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EThe%20preferred%20option%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20chances%20of%20fully%20implementing%20such%20a%20plan%2C%20which%20would%20amount%20to%20the%20total%20ethnic%20cleansing%20of%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%2C%20are%20negligible%20in%20many%20respects.%20Egyptian%20President%20Abdel%20Fattah%20el-Sisi%20has%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Fegypt-rejects-any-displacement-palestinians-into-sinai-says-sisi-2023-10-18%2F%5C%22%3Edeclared%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0that%20he%20strongly%20opposes%20opening%20the%20Rafah%20Crossing%20to%20absorb%20the%20Palestinian%20population%20from%20Gaza.%20He%20argued%20that%20the%20displacement%20of%20Palestinians%20to%20the%20Sinai%20would%20threaten%20Israeli%20peace%20with%20Egypt%2C%20and%20warned%20that%20it%20would%20lead%20to%20Palestinians%20using%20Egyptian%20territory%20as%20a%20base%20to%20continue%20armed%20confrontations%20with%20Israel.%20A%20similar%20plan%20has%20been%20presented%20in%20the%20past%20by%20Israeli%20officials%2C%20and%20until%20now%2C%20it%20too%20had%20not%20matured%20into%20a%20serious%20policy%20discussion.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMoreover%2C%20after%20weeks%20of%20reports%20that%20the%20United%20States%20was%20attempting%20to%20raise%20the%20possibility%20of%20moving%20Palestinians%20to%20Egypt%20as%20part%20of%20a%20%E2%80%9Chumanitarian%20corridor%2C%E2%80%9D%20U.S.%20President%20Joe%20Biden%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FPOTUS%2Fstatus%2F1718740437249245326%5C%22%3Easserted%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0yesterday%20that%20he%20and%20Sisi%20were%20committed%20to%20%E2%80%9Censuring%20that%20Palestinians%20in%20Gaza%20are%20not%20displaced%20to%20Egypt%20or%20any%20other%20nation.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Intelligence%20Ministry%20document%20states%20that%20Egypt%20will%20have%20an%20%E2%80%9Cobligation%20under%20international%20law%20to%20allow%20the%20passage%20of%20the%20population%2C%E2%80%9D%20and%20that%20the%20United%20States%20can%20contribute%20to%20the%20process%20by%20%E2%80%9Cexerting%20pressure%20on%20Egypt%2C%20Turkey%2C%20Qatar%2C%20Saudi%20Arabia%2C%20and%20the%20UAE%20to%20contribute%20to%20the%20initiative%2C%20either%20with%20resources%20or%20with%20the%20absorption%20of%20displaced%20persons.%E2%80%9D%20It%20also%20proposes%20conducting%20a%20dedicated%20public%20campaign%20aimed%20at%20the%20Arab%20world%2C%20with%20a%20%E2%80%9Cfocus%20on%20the%20message%20of%20assisting%20the%20Palestinian%20brothers%20and%20rehabilitating%20them%2C%20even%20at%20the%20price%20of%20a%20tone%20that%20rebukes%20or%20even%20harms%20Israel.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20the%20document%20notes%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Clarge-scale%20migration%E2%80%9D%20of%20non-combatants%20from%20combat%20zones%20is%20a%20%E2%80%9Cnatural%20and%20sought-after%20outcome%E2%80%9D%20that%20has%20also%20occurred%20in%20Syria%2C%20Afghanistan%2C%20and%20Ukraine%2C%20concluding%20that%20only%20the%20expulsion%20of%20the%20Palestinian%20population%20will%20constitute%20%E2%80%9Can%20appropriate%20response%20%5Bthat%5D%20will%20enable%20the%20creation%20of%20significant%20deterrence%20in%20the%20entire%20region.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20document%20presents%20two%20other%20options%20regarding%20what%20to%20do%20with%20the%20residents%20of%20Gaza%20the%20day%20after%20the%20war.%20The%20first%20is%20to%20allow%20the%20Palestinian%20Authority%20(PA)%2C%20headed%20by%20the%20Fatah%20party%20in%20the%20occupied%20West%20Bank%2C%20to%20rule%20Gaza%20under%20Israeli%20auspices.%20The%20second%20is%20to%20cultivate%20another%20%E2%80%9Clocal%20Arab%20authority%E2%80%9D%20as%20an%20alternative%20to%20Hamas.%20Both%20options%2C%20the%20document%20claims%2C%20are%20undesirable%20for%20Israel%20from%20a%20strategic%20and%20security%20perspective%2C%20and%20will%20not%20provide%20a%20sufficient%20message%20of%20deterrence%2C%20especially%20to%20Hezbollah%20in%20Lebanon.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20authors%20of%20the%20study%20also%20noted%20that%20bringing%20the%20PA%20into%20Gaza%20was%20the%20most%20dangerous%20option%20of%20the%20three%2C%20because%20it%20could%20lead%20to%20the%20establishment%20of%20a%20Palestinian%20state.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20division%20between%20the%20Palestinian%20population%20in%20Judea%20and%20Samaria%20and%20Gaza%20is%20one%20of%20the%20main%20obstacles%20today%20preventing%20the%20establishment%20of%20a%20Palestinian%20state.%20It%20is%20inconceivable%20that%20the%20outcome%20of%20this%20attack%20%5BHamas%E2%80%99%20Oct.%207%20massacres%5D%20will%20be%20an%20unprecedented%20victory%20for%20the%20Palestinian%20national%20movement%20and%20a%20path%20to%20the%20creation%20of%20a%20Palestinian%20state%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20document%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20document%20further%20argues%20that%20a%20model%20of%20Israeli%20military%20rule%20and%20PA%20civilian%20rule%2C%20as%20exists%20in%20the%20West%20Bank%2C%20is%20likely%20to%20fail%20in%20Gaza.%20%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20no%20way%20to%20maintain%20an%20effective%20military%20occupation%20in%20Gaza%20only%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20military%20presence%20without%20%5BIsraeli%5D%20settlements%2C%20and%20within%20a%20short%20time%20there%20will%20be%20internal%20Israeli%20and%20international%20pressure%20for%20withdrawal.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20authors%20added%20that%20in%20such%20a%20situation%2C%20the%20State%20of%20Israel%20%E2%80%9Cwill%20be%20considered%20a%20colonial%20power%20with%20an%20occupying%20army%20%E2%80%93%20similar%20to%20the%20current%20situation%20in%20Judea%20and%20Samaria%2C%20but%20even%20worse.%E2%80%9D%20They%20noted%20that%20the%20PA%20has%20low%20legitimacy%20among%20the%20Palestinian%20public%2C%20and%20that%20based%20on%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20previous%20experience%20of%20handing%20over%20control%20of%20Gaza%20to%20the%20PA%20and%20Hamas%E2%80%99%20eventual%20takeover%2C%20Israel%20should%20not%20%E2%80%9Crepeat%20the%20same%20mistake%20that%20led%20to%20the%20current%20situation.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20other%20option%2C%20the%20formation%20of%20a%20local%20Arab%20leadership%20to%20replace%20Hamas%2C%20is%20undesirable%20according%20to%20the%20document%2C%20because%20there%20are%20no%20local%20opposition%20movements%20to%20Hamas%20and%20a%20new%20leadership%20is%20liable%20to%20be%20more%20radical.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20most%20plausible%20scenario%20is%20%E2%80%A6%20not%20an%20ideological%20shift%20but%20rather%20the%20emergence%20of%20new%2C%20possibly%20even%20more%20extreme%2C%20Islamist%20movements%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%20The%20authors%20mention%20the%20necessity%20of%20%E2%80%9Ccreating%20ideological%20change%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20Palestinian%20population%20through%20a%20process%20of%20what%20it%20likens%20to%20%E2%80%9Cde-Nazification%2C%E2%80%9D%20requiring%20Israel%20to%20%E2%80%9Cdictate%20the%20school%20curricula%20and%20enforce%20its%20use%20for%20an%20entire%20generation.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20the%20document%20argued%20that%20if%20Gaza%E2%80%99s%20population%20remained%20in%20the%20strip%2C%20there%20would%20be%20%E2%80%9Cmany%20Arab%20casualties%E2%80%9D%20during%20the%20anticipated%20re-occupation%20of%20the%20territory%2C%20which%20would%20damage%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20international%20image%20even%20more%20than%20expelling%20the%20population.%20For%20all%20these%20reasons%2C%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Intelligence%E2%80%99s%20recommendation%20is%20to%20promote%20the%20permanent%20transfer%20of%20all%20Palestinian%20civilians%20from%20Gaza%20to%20the%20Sinai.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Defense%20Ministry%2C%20the%20army%20spokesperson%E2%80%99s%20office%2C%20and%20the%20Misgav%20Institute%20did%20not%20yet%20respond%20to%20%2B972%E2%80%99s%20requests%20for%20comment%20by%20the%20time%20of%20this%20article%E2%80%99s%20publication.%20Any%20responses%20received%20will%20be%20added%20here.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3EThis%20article%20first%20appeared%20on%3C%2Fi%3E%20%2B972%20Magazine%3Ci%3E.%20Read%20it%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.972mag.com%2Fintelligence-ministry-gaza-population-transfer%2F%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E.%20A%20version%20of%20this%20article%20was%20first%20published%20in%20Hebrew%20on%20%3C%2Fi%3ELocal%20Call%3Ci%3E.%20Read%20it%20%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mekomit.co.il%2F%25d7%2594%25d7%259e%25d7%25a1%25d7%259e%25d7%259a-%25d7%2594%25d7%259e%25d7%259c%25d7%2590-%25d7%25a9%25d7%259c-%25d7%259e%25d7%25a9%25d7%25a8%25d7%2593-%25d7%2594%25d7%259e%25d7%2595%25d7%2593%25d7%2599%25d7%25a2%25d7%2599%25d7%259f-%25d7%259b%25d7%2599%25d7%2591%25d7%2595%25d7%25a9-%25d7%25a2%25d7%2596%25d7%2594-%25d7%2595%2F%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3Ehere%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698817848000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F01111519%2Fimage1170x530cropped.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fisraeli-government-population-transfer-gaza-strip%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22An%20Intelligence%20Ministry%20document%20revealed%20by%20Local%20Call%20and%20%2B972%20shows%20how%20the%20idea%20of%20population%20transfer%20to%20the%20Sinai%20is%20reaching%20official%20discussions.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A8%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fisraeli-government-population-transfer-gaza-strip